with her report on the pioneers.

246
00:15:17,459 --> 00:15:20,795
That is so made up!

247
00:15:21,046 --> 00:15:22,672
Oh, my God! Tomorrow?

248
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:24,591
That's...
No, it's perfect.

249
00:15:24,841 --> 00:15:27,010
Oh, God!
Thank you so much!

250
00:15:27,260 --> 00:15:28,928
Great.

251
00:15:29,179 --> 00:15:31,181
I got the interview!

252
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:32,223
There you go!

253
00:15:32,474 --> 00:15:35,518
He even offered to meet me for lunch
and prep me for it.

254
00:15:35,769 --> 00:15:37,312
That is amazing!

255
00:15:37,562 --> 00:15:41,608
Well, if I know Mark,
and I think I do...

256
00:15:41,858 --> 00:15:43,318
...I'd expect nothing less.

257
00:15:43,568 --> 00:15:45,028
I gotta figure out what to wear.

258
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:49,157
High collar and baggy pants say,
"I'm a pro!"

259
00:15:49,407 --> 00:15:50,450
Yeah, right.

260
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,911
Okay, I'll see you guys later.

261
00:15:53,161 --> 00:15:55,246
You go get them!

262
00:15:55,497 --> 00:15:58,958
What did I do to you?
Did I hurt you in some way?

263
00:15:59,209 --> 00:16:00,001
What?

264
00:16:00,251 --> 00:16:02,671
"Why don't you call him?"

265
00:16:02,921 --> 00:16:06,341
Thank you very much.
Now he's gonna prep her...

266
00:16:06,591 --> 00:16:10,804
...as in what you do before
you surgically remove the boyfriend!

267
00:16:11,054 --> 00:16:11,971
Are you crazy?

268
00:16:12,222 --> 00:16:17,185
Am I? Am I out of my mind?
Am I losing my senses?

269
00:16:17,477 --> 00:16:20,897
This dreamy guy's taking my girlfriend
out for a meal!

270
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:22,857
This isn't even about you!

271
00:16:23,108 --> 00:16:25,944
It's about something wonderful
happening for Rachel.

272
00:16:26,194 --> 00:16:28,947
Even if you're right,
and he wants to sleep with her...

273
00:16:29,197 --> 00:16:31,032
...does that mean he gets to?

274
00:16:31,282 --> 00:16:34,744
- No, but...
- Don't you trust her?

275
00:16:34,786 --> 00:16:38,873
Then get over yourself!
Grow up!

276
00:16:41,543 --> 00:16:44,713
You grow up.

277
00:16:54,806 --> 00:16:58,018
This tiramisu is excellent.

278
00:16:58,268 --> 00:16:59,936
Did you make it, Mary Angela?

279
00:17:00,186 --> 00:17:02,522
No, I did.

280
00:17:02,772 --> 00:17:05,316
Well, it's yummy.

281
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:06,526
So...

282
00:17:06,776 --> 00:17:09,237
Mary Angela, do you like it?

283
00:17:09,487 --> 00:17:13,283
Of course.
It's her favorite.

284
00:17:13,992 --> 00:17:15,744
So...

285
00:17:15,994 --> 00:17:18,705
Mary Angela, what's
your second favorite?

286
00:17:18,955 --> 00:17:20,498
More of Grandma's tiramisu.

287
00:17:20,749 --> 00:17:24,544
Oh, would you just please...

288
00:17:24,961 --> 00:17:28,882
...give me your recipe, because
this is great! It's topnotch!

289
00:17:29,132 --> 00:17:30,216
That dies with me.

290
00:17:30,467 --> 00:17:33,303
So will I.

291
00:17:33,928 --> 00:17:36,181
Excuse yourself
and go to the bathroom.

292
00:17:36,431 --> 00:17:38,767
I was just squinting.
It doesn't mean anything.

293
00:17:39,017 --> 00:17:41,853
Just do it!

294
00:17:46,149 --> 00:17:49,778
Will you excuse me, I have to...

295
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:03,875
Finally! I thought we'd
never be alone.

296
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:05,752
Can I just tell you something?

297
00:18:06,002 --> 00:18:10,507
I have not stopped thinking about you
since the party.

298
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:15,887
Look, I may have jumped the gun here.

299
00:18:16,346 --> 00:18:18,098
I just got out of a relationship.

300
00:18:18,348 --> 00:18:20,350
And I'm not really in a...

301
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,227
...in a commitment kind of place.

302
00:18:22,477 --> 00:18:23,478
So? Me neither!

303
00:18:23,728 --> 00:18:28,608
God, Mary Angela was right.
You do have the softest lips.

304
00:18:28,942 --> 00:18:30,568
You're not Mary Angela?

305
00:18:30,819 --> 00:18:33,071
No! I'm Mary Therese!

306
00:18:33,321 --> 00:18:35,156
This is so bad.

307
00:18:35,407 --> 00:18:38,159
If you're not Mary Angela,
then who is?

308
00:18:38,410 --> 00:18:41,079
I am.

309
00:18:41,162 --> 00:18:44,416
Oh, it's so bad.

310
00:18:44,749 --> 00:18:47,711
No, Joey! No, Joey!

311
00:18:47,961 --> 00:18:50,338
What's going on?

312
00:18:50,588 --> 00:18:53,758
You're it!
Now run and hide!

313
00:18:54,009 --> 00:18:56,594
It's no big deal.
Chandler was just kissing me...

314
00:18:56,845 --> 00:18:58,763
...because he thought
I was Mary Angela.

315
00:18:59,014 --> 00:19:01,933
What? How could you
think she was Mary Angela?

316
00:19:02,183 --> 00:19:06,438
I wasn't sure which one
Mary Angela was.

317
00:19:06,688 --> 00:19:08,773
Look, I'm sorry.
I was really drunk...

318
00:19:09,024 --> 00:19:11,317
...and you guys
all look really similar.

319
00:19:11,568 --> 00:19:14,320
- I say punch him, Joey!
- Yeah, punch him!

320
00:19:14,571 --> 00:19:15,864
We should all calm down...

321
00:19:16,114 --> 00:19:19,200
...because your brother's
not gonna punch me.

322
00:19:19,451 --> 00:19:21,286
Are you?

323
00:19:21,536 --> 00:19:23,163
That's usually what I'd do.

324
00:19:23,413 --> 00:19:25,832
But I never thought you'd be
on the receiving end.

325
00:19:26,082 --> 00:19:27,625
How could you do this?

326
00:19:27,876 --> 00:19:30,211
If you wanna punch me, go ahead.
I deserve it.

327
00:19:30,462 --> 00:19:34,758
But I want you to know that I'd never
soberly hurt you or your family.

328
00:19:35,008 --> 00:19:36,801
You're my best friend.

329
00:19:37,052 --> 00:19:41,348
And I'd never do anything
like this, ever again.

330
00:19:41,765 --> 00:19:42,766
So what?

331
00:19:43,016 --> 00:19:46,770
- I say punch him!
- Yeah, punch him!

332
00:19:47,020 --> 00:19:50,065
No, I'm not gonna punch Chandler.

333
00:19:50,315 --> 00:19:52,484
- I'll do it.
- No, you won't!

334
00:19:52,734 --> 00:19:56,488
He knows he did a terrible thing,
and I believe him. He's sorry.

335
00:19:56,738 --> 00:19:58,740
But you got one more apology to make.

336
00:19:58,990 --> 00:20:01,659
You gotta apologize to Mary Angela.

337
00:20:01,910 --> 00:20:05,121
- Absolutely. You got it.
- All right.

338
00:20:13,922 --> 00:20:17,384
- Cookie, now you can punch him!
- What?

339
00:20:24,849 --> 00:20:26,309
What are you doing here?

340
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:31,106
You know, this building's
on my paper route, so...

341
00:20:31,606 --> 00:20:32,899
How did it go?

342
00:20:33,149 --> 00:20:35,735
The woman I interviewed with
was pretty tough...

343
00:20:35,985 --> 00:20:37,821
...but thank God Mark coached me.

344
00:20:38,071 --> 00:20:40,782
Once I talked about the Fall line,
she got all happy.

345
00:20:41,032 --> 00:20:44,411
- I'm so proud of you.
- Me too!

346
00:20:44,661 --> 00:20:46,871
Listen, I'm...

347
00:20:47,122 --> 00:20:51,376
I'm sorry I've been
so crazy and jealous and...

348
00:20:51,626 --> 00:20:53,878
It's just,
I like you a lot, so...

349
00:20:54,129 --> 00:20:56,631
I know.

350
00:20:57,674 --> 00:20:58,800
- Hi.
- Hi, Mark.

351
00:20:59,050 --> 00:21:03,054
I just talked to Joanna,
and she loves you. You got the job.

352
00:21:03,304 --> 00:21:05,140
I did?

353
00:21:05,390 --> 00:21:06,641
Oh, my God!

354
00:21:06,891 --> 00:21:10,895
Congratulations...

355
00:21:14,482 --> 00:21:15,942
So, Phoebe?

356
00:21:16,192 --> 00:21:17,110
How was your date?

357
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:19,320
Oh, well, you know...

358
00:21:19,571 --> 00:21:21,990
Yeah, I do know.

359
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:23,491
You were eavesdropping?

360
00:21:23,742 --> 00:21:29,247
Eavesdropping? Pheebs, the ceiling
tiles were falling down.

361
00:21:29,414 --> 00:21:30,915
Oh, I'm sorry.

362
00:21:31,166 --> 00:21:37,839
But I really like this guy
and I think he really likes me.

363
00:21:41,676 --> 00:21:42,761
Maybe he's just...

364
00:21:43,011 --> 00:21:47,766
...jumping on a pogo stick
and he really likes it.

365
00:21:49,934 --> 00:21:53,521
Maybe the pogo stick likes it too.

366
00:21:53,855 --> 00:21:56,566
All right, that's it.
He cannot do this to Phoebe!

367
00:21:56,816 --> 00:21:59,986
This guy's gonna get
the butt-kicking of a lifetime!

368
00:22:00,236 --> 00:22:02,489
But is he a big guy?

369
00:22:02,739 --> 00:22:03,907
We'll all go. Come on.

370
00:22:04,157 --> 00:22:05,742
Thanks, you guys.
Thank you!

371
00:22:05,992 --> 00:22:07,202
Don't worry!

372
00:22:07,452 --> 00:22:10,497
God!
I hope they kick his ass!

373
00:22:10,747 --> 00:22:12,123
Honey, I'm sorry.

374
00:22:12,374 --> 00:22:13,958
If it's any consolation...

375
00:22:14,209 --> 00:22:18,588
...he sounded like
he had more fun with you.
